cff-version: 1.2.0
title: >-
  Darija-ASR: A Controlled Comparison of End-to-End and
  Cascaded Architectures for Moroccan Darija Speech
  Recognition
message: >-
  If you use this code or the fine-tuned models, please
  cite this repository and the supporting frameworks
  (Marco-ASR, Casablanca normalization, base models).
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Ouhmd
    given-names: Souhail
    orcid: 'https://orcid.org/0000-0000-0000-0000'  # TODO: replace with your ORCID if you have one
repository-code: 'https://github.com/Tilas/darija-asr-comparison'
url: 'https://github.com/Tilas/darija-asr-comparison'
abstract: >-
  Phase 1 of a PFE comparing an end-to-end audio-LLM
  (Qwen2-Audio-7B-Instruct) against a cascaded ASR
  encoder-decoder (Whisper-Large-v3) for Moroccan Darija
  speech recognition. Both models are fine-tuned with LoRA
  on MoulSot under the Marco-ASR adaptive learning-rate
  framework, with statistically rigorous evaluation
  (paired-bootstrap CIs, code-switching partitioning, OOD
  generalization). Whisper-LV3 outperforms Qwen2-Audio-7B
  at every training scale and on every partition,
  including OOD audio, while training 2.6x faster.
keywords:
  - speech-recognition
  - asr
  - moroccan-darija
  - arabic
  - whisper
  - qwen2-audio
  - lora
  - peft
  - low-resource-asr
  - code-switching
  - marco-asr
license: MIT
